The paper discusses the use of neuroevolution and coevolution in the training of GANs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, specifically Fashion-MNIST and MNIST, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) research. The paper also discusses the use of GANs as a generative model, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of adversarial strategies in the training algorithm, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT).
